===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
In the {{w|oracle bone script}}, an {{liushu|ic|nocap=y}}: {{zh-l|*午}} (“pestle”, the original form of {{zh-l|*杵}}) + {{zh-l|*廾|two hands}} + two {{zh-l|*禾|grain}}. The most conservative variant is [[𥢮]]. A form of its bronze inscription containing only one {{zh-l|*禾}} developed into the subsequent small seal script form in ''{{w|Shuowen}}''. The 午 and 廾 components have fused into {{zh-l|*𡗗}} in the modern form.

According to ''{{w|Shuowen Jiezi}}'', the glyph is an {{Han compound|舂|禾|t1=to pound grain|t2=grain|ls=ic|abb1=y|nocap=y}} – husked grain. However this would necessitate a phonological shift that is considered unlikely, and furthermore is likely a [[folk etymology]] altogether.<ref>{{cite-web |url=http://www.zdic.net/z/20/sw/79E6.htm |title=秦, Qin |work=zdic.net}}</ref>

