===Definitions===
{{head|zh|hanzi}}

# {{lb|zh|obsolete}} [[grain]]; a specific variety of grain; to [[pound]] grain
#* {{zh-x|秦，禾 名。|Qin is a name of a grain.|ref=Shuowen}}
# {{lb|zh|historical}} [[Qin]] (an ancient [[fief]] and city, the origin of the state)
#*: {{zh-x|非子 居 ^犬丘，……^孝王 封 ^非子 為 附庸，邑 之 於 ^秦。|Feizi resided in Quanqiu... [Zhou] King Xiao enfeoffed Feizi as a vassal and gave him the settlement at '''Qin''' (modern-day Tianshui/Zhangjiachuan, Gansu).|ref=Shiji}}
# {{lb|zh|historical}} {{zh-div|國}} [[State of Qin]] (in ancient [[China]], rising to power in the [[Warring States]] period)
#* {{zh-x|^晉 侯、^秦 伯 圍 ^鄭，以 其 無禮 於 ^晉，且 貳 於 ^楚 也。^晉 軍 ^函陵，^秦 軍 ^氾南。|The Marquis of Jin and the Earl of '''Qin''' laid siege to [the capital of] Zheng, under the pretext of the [Earl of] Zheng's disrespectful treatments towards [Marquis of] Jin and double-mindedness towards Chu. Jin armies were stationed at Hanling; '''Qin''' armies at Fannan.|ref=Zuozhuan}}
# {{lb|zh|historical}} {{zh-div|朝}} [[Qin]] [[dynasty]] (221–206 BC), the first [[imperial]] dynasty of unified China
# {{lb|zh|historical|by extension}} [[China]] (an [[exonym]] used by the [[Xiongnu]], in the [[Western Regions]], and in ancient [[India]]/[[Rome]])
#* {{zh-x|^匈奴 縛 馬 前後 足，置 城 下，馳 言：「^秦 人，我 匄{gài} 若 馬。」|The Xiongnu bound the front and back legs of the horses, placed them under the city wall, and galloped by shouting: "Men of '''Qin''' [Chinese], we beg you for these horses."|ref=Hanshu}}
#* {{zh-x|昔 為 形 與 影，今 為 ^胡 與 ^秦。|In the past we were like a body and its shadow [inseparable]; today we are like the Hu [barbarians] and the '''Qin''' [Chinese] [enemies/separated].|ref={{w|Fu Xuan}}, ''Yuzhang Xing'' ({{lang|zh|豫章行}})}}
# [[Shaanxi]] province (an abbreviation derived from the ancient state's location)
#: {{zh-x|^秦 ^腔|'''Shaanxi''' opera}}
#: {{zh-x|^三 ^秦|The Three '''Qins''' (referring to Northern, Central and Southern Shaanxi)}}
# {{lb|zh|historical}} Name of several dynasties or states in Chinese history (Sixteen Kingdoms period, etc.)
## {{w|Former Qin}} (351–394)
## {{w|Later Qin}} (384–417)
## {{w|Western Qin}} (385–431)
# {{lb|zh|historical|rare}} Name of an ancient township in the State of [[Lu]] (modern-day [[Fan County]], [[Henan]])
#* {{zh-x|秋，築 臺 于 ^秦。|In autumn, a terrace was built at '''Qin'''.|ref=Zuozhuan}}
# {{lb|zh|literary|botany}} A specific [[fragrant]] [[herb]] (often cited as {{zh-l|*秦衡}})
#* {{zh-x|獵 蕙 草，離 ^秦 衡。|Gathering the hui plants, passing through the '''qin'''heng.|ref={{w|Song Yu}}, ''Feng Fu'' ({{lang|zh|風賦}})}}
# {{surname|zh}}
#: {{zh-x|^秦 ^良-玉|{{w|Qin Liangyu|'''Qin''' Liangyu}} (Ming dynasty female general)}}
#: {{zh-x|^關.^公 戰 ^秦 ^瓊|{{w|Guan Yu}} fights {{w|Qin Qiong|'''Qin''' Qiong}} (anachronistic battle)}}

